DI/USDT funding rates using a premium/discount mechanism relative to the spot index price. The platform applies a dampening factor to prevent extreme rates, typically capping daily funding at ±0.375%. Funding payments occur automatically in your USDT margin balance, with long positions paying shorts when rates are positive. BingX's social trading focus means funding rates can be influenced by copy trading activity and retail sentiment around Bitcoin Ordinals."}]]}],"$L3",["$L4","$L5","$L6"],"$L7"]}],"$L8"]}]]}],["$L9","$La"],"$Lb"]}],"loading":null,"isPartial":false}
3:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","ORDI","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ORDI represents the first BRC-20 token on Bitcoin via the Ordinals protocol, creating unique arbitrage dynamics. The pair exhibits higher volatility than major cryptocurrencies, leading to more frequent funding rate opportunities. Small trading volume on BingX can amplify funding rate variations, especially during Bitcoin network narrative shifts."}]]}]
4:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ORDI/USDT funding rates on BingX have shown correlation with Bitcoin network activity and Ordinals inscription volume. During periods of high Bitcoin Ordinals hype, funding rates frequently turn positive as retail traders take leveraged long positions. The pair typically experiences funding rate spikes of 0.05-0.15% during major Bitcoin ecosystem announcements. Weekend sessions often see reduced funding volatility due to lower institutional activity, while Asian trading hours show higher funding variation due to retail participation."}]]}]
5:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ORDI funding arbitrage on BingX benefits from the platform's social trading features, where copy traders can amplify position imbalances. Cross-exchange arbitrage with major platforms like Binance or OKX becomes profitable when BingX rates deviate by more than 0.03% after accounting for transfer costs. Grid trading bots on BingX can automate funding collection strategies by maintaining market-neutral positions. The 8-hour funding interval provides sufficient time for position adjustments, unlike exchanges with hourly settlements."}]]}]
6:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BingX's lower liquidity for ORDI/USDT increases slippage risks during position entry and exit, particularly for larger arbitrage sizes. The exchange's focus on retail traders creates higher volatility in funding rates compared to institutional-heavy platforms. Smart contract risks specific to BRC-20 tokens and Bitcoin network congestion can affect ORDI price discovery and funding calculations. Limited advanced order types on BingX may restrict sophisticated arbitrage strategies compared to professional trading platforms."}]]}]
7:["$","$Lc",null,{"items":[{"question":"What are typical ORDI/USDT funding rates on BingX?","answer":"ORDI funding rates on BingX typically range from -0.05% to +0.15% per 8-hour session, with higher positive rates during Bitcoin Ordinals narrative cycles. Extreme rates above 0.2% occur during major market events or low liquidity periods."},{"question":"How does BingX's copy trading affect ORDI funding rates?","answer":"Copy trading on BingX can create asymmetric position flows in ORDI perpetuals, leading to higher funding rate volatility. When popular traders take large ORDI positions, their copiers amplify the market imbalance, often driving funding rates to extremes."},{"question":"What's the minimum position size for ORDI arbitrage on BingX?","answer":"BingX typically requires minimum positions of 1 ORDI for perpetual contracts. However, profitable funding arbitrage usually requires larger positions due to the 0.05% taker fee structure and funding rate variations."},{"question":"How does ORDI funding compare to other Bitcoin ecosystem tokens on BingX?","answer":"ORDI generally shows higher funding rate volatility than established tokens due to its smaller market cap and narrative-driven price action. The token's connection to Bitcoin Ordinals creates unique funding patterns compared to Lightning Network or sidechain tokens."}]}]
